![preview](/assets/preview.png)

- VitalsWidget moves system monitoring from the top panel directly onto your desktop, inspired by modern, minimal UI design.

## Features
1. Real-time Monitoring
2. Elegant Ring Design - Circular progress rings with centered SVG icons that adapt to your theme.
3. Floating Workspace - Position the widget anywhere on your screen using precise percentage-based coordinates.
4. Colors Customization - Individual ring colors, background, and borders.
5. Layout Customization - Adjustable circle diameter, ring thickness, and spacing.
6. Visibility - Toggle labels and icons to match your aesthetic.
7. GPU Support - Native support for both NVIDIA (`nvidia-smi`) and AMD (`radeontop`).


##  Installation

## Prerequisites
### Requirements

1. GNOME Shell - [45, 46, 47, 48, or 49 ]
2. Node.js - 18+ 
3. TypeScript - 5.3+ 

# 1. Clone the repository
git clone [https://github.com/ctrln3rd/vitals-widget.git](https://github.com/ctrln3rd/vitals-widget.git)
cd vitals-widget

# 2. Install dev dependencies
npm install

# 3. Build and install to local extensions folder
make install

# 4. Enable the extension
gnome-extensions enable vitalswidget@ctrln3rd.github.com
